         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translations</head>
            <div  type="translation" source="#oliverioDAI" xml:lang="it"><p>L'Imperatore Cesare Marco Aurelio Claudio Augusto, con le armi dopo aver stroncato l'annosa 
            dei Marmaridai (beduina) oltracotanza, Claudiopoli, sua eponima di nuovo (sana pianta) costrui, dirigendo le operazioni militari e provvedendo all costruzione 
            dell'abitato Probo, l'illustrissimo Prefetto d'Egitto.</p></div>
            <div type="translation" source="#edd" xml:lang="en"><p>Emperor Caesar Marcus Aurelius Claudius Augustus, having removed, with arms, the longlasting savagery of the Marmaritae, 
               founded Claudiopolis as new, called after himself;
               Probus, the excellent prefect of Egypt, conducted the war and undertook the foundation.</p></div>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>line 1 Claudius II Gothicus, emperor 268 - 270; <bibl><title>PLRE</title> <citedRange>I, Claudius 11</citedRange></bibl></p>
            <p>l.3 This is the only certain evidence for third century raiding of Cyrenaica.
                 <!--For the activities of the Marmaridae see Introduction,--></p>
            <p> line 4 This must refer to a refoundation and renaming of Cyrene itself. The new name was presumably very short-lived, but it is possible that it is this event 
                    that lies behind the description of Cyrene as a colony in the Peutinger Table <!--, see introduction--> </p>
            <p> line 5 Tenagino Probus, <foreign xml:lang="la">praefectus Aegypti</foreign>; <bibl>
                  <title>PLRE</title> <citedRange>I, Probus 8</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
         </div>
         
